The old man and I have enough problems.

258
00:23:34,321 --> 00:23:38,242
We're tryin' to make as much money
as we can before we lose this place.

259
00:23:38,325 --> 00:23:42,997
What do you mean, lose this place?
You ain't gonna lose this place.

260
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:46,250
- It's a landmark.
- That don't mean shit, homes.

261
00:23:46,333 --> 00:23:49,169
If money talks
and bullshit walks, we walkin'.

262
00:23:49,253 --> 00:23:51,839
And it ain't gonna be down easy street.

263
00:23:51,922 --> 00:23:53,507
What's the story, old man?

264
00:23:53,590 --> 00:24:00,931
In '56 I leased this property when nobody
wanted to be seen on this side of the hill.

265
00:24:01,014 --> 00:24:06,687
And in '66 I renewed my lease
on my own terms.

266
00:24:08,105 --> 00:24:10,941
350 a month for 30 years.

267
00:24:12,276 --> 00:24:15,862
In 21 days those 30 years have run out.

268
00:24:15,946 --> 00:24:19,032
Now with the whole world
flyin' into Burbank,

269
00:24:19,116 --> 00:24:25,372
they're tryin' to strong-arm us
for $2.5 million for a five-year lease.

270
00:24:26,540 --> 00:24:30,127
They're gonna put up another skyscraper.

271
00:24:34,381 --> 00:24:38,218
- Who's tryin' to strong-arm you?
- The bank.

272
00:24:40,220 --> 00:24:43,723
- What bank?
- Great Trust.

273
00:24:47,477 --> 00:24:51,231
- The suits?
- Hm-hmm.

274
00:24:53,566 --> 00:24:55,402
Well...

275
00:24:55,485 --> 00:25:00,407
there's only one place
to get that kind of money so fast.

276
00:25:00,490 --> 00:25:04,828
- No suit's gonna loan us $2.5 million.
- (old man) That's for sure.

277
00:25:04,911 --> 00:25:07,914
Man, I ain't talkin' about no loan.

278
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:14,671
- I don't wanna hear it, Harley.
- Hear what?

279
00:25:14,754 --> 00:25:18,007
- You don't wanna know.
- Know what?

280
00:25:18,091 --> 00:25:20,927
He's gonna say we should rob the bank.

281
00:25:21,010 --> 00:25:25,515
We ain't gonna rob any damn bank.
We ain't bank robbers.

282
00:25:25,598 --> 00:25:29,269
We owe it to the old man.
We grew up in this place.

283
00:25:29,352 --> 00:25:31,771
You boys don't owe me anything.

284
00:25:32,438 --> 00:25:34,357
(Harley) Sure, we do.

285
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:38,695
Hell, if it wasn't for you,
we'd all be face-down in the gutter

286
00:25:38,778 --> 00:25:42,698
with a cigarette for company and a...

287
00:25:42,782 --> 00:25:45,284
a needle for good times.

288
00:25:49,038 --> 00:25:51,541
I'm ready to go.

289
00:25:51,624 --> 00:25:54,126
- OK, baby. In a minute.
- Now!

290
00:25:59,966 --> 00:26:04,887
Count me out of this one.
I made a promise to Lulu.

291
00:26:07,056 --> 00:26:09,308
You made me a lot of promises, Jack.

292
00:26:09,392 --> 00:26:12,645
We were gonna have a baby someday.

293
00:26:12,728 --> 00:26:16,065
Can't start a family from behind bars.

294
00:26:20,403 --> 00:26:24,824
You know... I really love this place.

295
00:26:25,658 --> 00:26:28,828
It's a home. Makes me feel good.

296
00:26:28,911 --> 00:26:33,499
And if we gotta rob a bank to save it,

297
00:26:34,667 --> 00:26:37,169
I'll do that.

298
00:26:37,253 --> 00:26:39,338
But I can't do it alone.

299
00:26:39,421 --> 00:26:43,259
You guys are gonna have to get it up too.

300
00:27:52,577 --> 00:27:56,581
(radio) 12 minutes Pacific and California.
We'll check with you then. Over.

301
00:27:56,665 --> 00:27:57,749
Roger, Dispatch.

302
00:28:02,754 --> 00:28:04,255
We copy.

303
00:28:08,927 --> 00:28:10,011
Shit!

304
00:28:54,722 --> 00:28:59,644
Car 3, this is Dispatch. Give me
your 10-20 and security code, over.

305
00:28:59,727 --> 00:29:02,647
Dispatch, we're at the shipyard.

306
00:29:05,566 --> 00:29:08,069
What's with this hard-hat?

307
00:29:08,653 --> 00:29:10,655
(horn)

308
00:29:20,581 --> 00:29:24,335
You'll have to move your equipment.
I got a delivery to make.

309
00:29:24,418 --> 00:29:28,005
Are you deaf?
I said you'll have to move your...

310
00:29:28,089 --> 00:29:30,091
I heard what you said.

311
00:29:31,759 --> 00:29:34,011
Drop your gun.

312
00:29:34,094 --> 00:29:36,347
You won't like what you're getting into.

313
00:29:36,430 --> 00:29:40,100
(Harley) From 15 feet away
there's a chance you could miss me.

314
00:29:40,184 --> 00:29:43,604
I could be blind and
still blow your head off, so drop it.

315
00:29:43,687 --> 00:29:45,773
No, you drop it, asshole.

316
00:29:48,359 --> 00:29:50,444
- Shit!
- Think fast.

317
00:29:56,033 --> 00:29:57,201
Shit!

318
00:29:58,619 --> 00:30:01,455
Come on. Get over here. Sit down.

319
00:30:03,957 --> 00:30:07,044
Guns are made to be shot, Harley,
not thrown.

320
00:30:07,961 --> 00:30:10,547
(Harley) Go do it, Jose.

321
00:30:10,631 --> 00:30:14,218
You're the deadest shot I've ever seen.
Where'd you learn to do that?

322
00:30:14,301 --> 00:30:16,720
Read a book. Came with the gun.

323
00:30:16,803 --> 00:30:18,722
Who are you guys?

324
00:30:18,805 --> 00:30:23,227
He's Harley Davidson
and I'm the Marlboro man.

325
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:27,064
You look like a bunch
of two-bit hoods to me.

326
00:30:32,986 --> 00:30:35,822
Does that look like the work
of two-bit hoods?

327
00:30:35,906 --> 00:30:38,992
Yeah. Pros would have used my keys.

328
00:30:40,744 --> 00:30:42,913
He likes to blow things up.

329
00:30:43,914 --> 00:30:45,582
Hot stuff. Watch it.

330
00:30:45,665 --> 00:30:50,670
- Nice day for work, huh, Jimmy?
- None better ever, homes.

331
00:30:58,595 --> 00:31:00,847
Nice doing business with you boys.

332
00:31:00,931 --> 00:31:05,018
Your business isn't with us. It's with them.

333
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:27,373
Whatever they've got to say,
I don't wanna hear it.

334
00:31:29,375 --> 00:31:31,878
- Let's rock it! We got company.
- Shit, no.

335
00:31:34,297 --> 00:31:35,215
Shit!

336
00:31:40,970 --> 00:31:43,389
What the fuck is all this about?

337
00:31:50,980 --> 00:31:55,068
Harley, throw that shotgun at 'em.
Maybe you'll hit somethin'.

338
00:32:02,825 --> 00:32:05,745
- I thought you was a dead shot.
- So did I.

339
00:32:05,828 --> 00:32:09,582
- Then why ain't they droppin'?
- Beats the shit outta me.

340
00:32:15,421 --> 00:32:17,340
(yelling)

341
00:32:34,690 --> 00:32:35,941
Come on, guys.

342
00:32:46,702 --> 00:32:49,788
- Come on, Harley!
- Let's go, Jimmy!

343
00:33:25,073 --> 00:33:29,328
(Jimmy) All right, you're a big fuckin'
hero, big man! A big fuckin' hero!

344
00:33:29,411 --> 00:33:32,998
You guys needed backup. I had
nothing to do and no one to do it with.

345
00:33:33,081 --> 00:33:37,669
Backup, hell. Harley's thinking
damn near had us on the ropes.

346
00:33:37,753 --> 00:33:39,588
Saved our lives, big boy.

347
00:33:39,671 --> 00:33:43,008
You guys owe me a bike.
I gotta get a new bike.

348
00:33:43,091 --> 00:33:45,093
Hey, man, you'll get a new bike.

349
00:33:45,177 --> 00:33:49,765
Promise you won't tell Lulu. I don't want
her mad. She's mean when she's mad.

350
00:33:49,848 --> 00:33:53,768
I can take care of the bike,
but I can't take care of the bitch.

351
00:33:53,852 --> 00:33:58,190
- Why not? You did once.
- You might wanna take a look at this shit.

352
00:34:04,362 --> 00:34:07,032
- What is it?
- Unmelted, pure Crystal Dream.

353
00:34:07,115 --> 00:34:10,201
What the fuck is that
and what is it doin' here?

354
00:34:10,285 --> 00:34:14,956
It's a drug. And I don't know
what the fuck it's doin' here.

355
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:18,960
I'm a son of a bitch.
We jumped the wrong train.

356
00:34:19,044 --> 00:34:20,962
Fuck! Shit, man!

357
00:34:22,213 --> 00:34:25,717
His little brother OD'd using this shit.

358
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:29,053
Don't worry, Jose, we ain't drug dealers.

359
00:34:32,557 --> 00:34:36,561
This is not a walk in the park, Harley.
This is way out there on the edge.

360
00:34:36,644 --> 00:34:40,732
These guys are killers. They killed
their own men tryin' to waste us.

361
00:34:40,815 --> 00:34:43,234
That's enough, Jimmy.

362
00:34:43,318 --> 00:34:46,571
I never liked this plan from the start.

363
00:34:46,654 --> 00:34:48,990
But you needed help and you took it.

364
00:34:49,073 --> 00:34:52,327
So don't whine about it now.

365
00:34:52,410 --> 00:34:55,163
What's done is done.
There's no turnin' back.

366
00:34:58,166 --> 00:34:59,917
Who are these men?

367
00:35:00,001 --> 00:35:03,671
Judging from the data we gathered,
they're dilettantes.

368
00:35:03,755 --> 00:35:10,344
Details would suggest that they were
not aware of the cargo they've stolen.

369
00:35:17,768 --> 00:35:22,857
If they're amateurs,
how'd they destroy two vehicles

370
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:26,944
and then manage to get away
with the goods?

371
00:35:28,612 --> 00:35:31,115
They were extremely lucky.

372
00:35:34,869 --> 00:35:39,540
I don't have time for luck, now, do I?

373
00:35:40,207 --> 00:35:42,626
Get back what's mine.

374
00:35:43,544 --> 00:35:47,047
And kill these men, Alexander, OK?

375
00:35:53,470 --> 00:35:54,972
Yeah, yeah, yeah

376
00:36:03,355 --> 00:36:05,816
Man, we really fucked up big.

377
00:36:08,986 --> 00:36:14,992
How was I supposed to know somebody's
using a bank as a front to run drugs?

378
00:36:15,993 --> 00:36:18,996
Harley, I'm tired and I'm pissed.

379
00:36:20,581 --> 00:36:23,083
And I'd just like to unwind.

380
00:36:24,459 --> 00:36:26,587
So stop thinkin'.

381
00:36:26,670 --> 00:36:30,257
Now I gotta think of some way
to make things right.

382
00:36:34,344 --> 00:36:36,430
Hi.

383
00:36:36,513 --> 00:36:40,017
I know you don't know me,
but I don't have a way home

384
00:36:40,100 --> 00:36:43,520
and Jimmy said that you'd give me a ride.

385
00:36:44,938 --> 00:36:47,649
Sure, I'll give you a ride, Sally.

386
00:36:47,691 --> 00:36:49,860
The name tag's wrong.

387
00:36:49,985 --> 00:36:52,070
My real name's Honey.

388
00:36:53,530 --> 00:36:57,367
Pure gold... and sweet.

389
00:36:59,536 --> 00:37:01,621
I'm off at ten.

390
00:37:03,290 --> 00:37:08,378
My old man used to tell me,
before he left this shitty world,

391
00:37:08,461 --> 00:37:11,965
the right woman can make you
and the wrong one can break you.

392
00:37:12,048 --> 00:37:14,551
I woke up one mornin'...

393
00:37:17,053 --> 00:37:19,139
and she was gone.

394
00:37:21,308 --> 00:37:24,227
No note. No kiss goodbye. No nothin'.

395
00:37:24,310 --> 00:37:28,314
And I still have feelings
for her deep inside.

396
00:37:29,482 --> 00:37:36,156
Partner, I only know of two cures
for that particular ailment.

397
00:37:36,906 --> 00:37:41,619
And since you don't drink any more,
you're down to one.

398
00:37:43,496 --> 00:37:45,915
Let me borrow your bike.

399
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:48,126
I gotta take Sally home.

400
00:37:48,167 --> 00:37:49,836
Get a cab.

401
00:38:06,644 --> 00:38:07,687
(siren)

402
00:39:04,577 --> 00:39:08,414
Stand up and put your hands
behind your head.

403
00:39:10,249 --> 00:39:12,751
I was just blowin' off a little steam.

404
00:39:12,835 --> 00:39:17,673
You blew in the wrong place.
Kiss the wall and spread 'em.

405
00:39:37,359 --> 00:39:40,362
OK, cowboy, let's blow off some steam.

406
00:39:46,034 --> 00:39:48,120
What's wrong tonight?

407
00:39:49,955 --> 00:39:52,040
I'm getting married.

408
00:39:54,292 --> 00:39:56,920
Goddamn you, Robert,
I'm tired of waiting

409
00:39:57,045 --> 00:39:59,756
for you to come by
when you feel the need.

410
00:39:59,881 --> 00:40:04,719
I get Ionely. I like to share my bed
with someone at night.

411
00:40:10,725 --> 00:40:13,728
Hell, isn't that what we're doin'?

412
00:40:14,646 --> 00:40:17,399
One, maybe two nights a month,
if I'm lucky.

413
00:40:18,817 --> 00:40:21,152
Well, I am what I am, Virginia.

414
00:40:21,236 --> 00:40:26,116
I've accepted that, even loved it.
But I don't have to like it.

415
00:40:28,827 --> 00:40:31,663
I get scared for you. I worry.

416
00:40:31,746 --> 00:40:36,793
You could spend the rest of your life
looking for what it is you're looking for,

417
00:40:36,835 --> 00:40:39,671
but someday you'll have to find yourself.

418
00:40:39,754 --> 00:40:43,424
I just can't wait for you to do it any more.

419
00:40:46,845 --> 00:40:48,930
I love you, Robert.

420
00:40:50,848 --> 00:40:55,436
But after tonight,
you're not welcome here any more.

421
00:41:13,204 --> 00:41:14,831
(rock music on radio)

422
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:39,230
Oh, fuck!

423
00:41:41,565 --> 00:41:46,404
That's for Marlboro. Me and you'll
go out and have somethin' to eat.

424
00:41:46,487 --> 00:41:48,322
You're a bad man, Harley.

425
00:41:51,992 --> 00:41:54,912
(Virginia)
What are you two up to this time?

426
00:41:57,998 --> 00:42:02,545
Do you know anything
about this new drug, Crystal Dream?

427
00:42:03,921 --> 00:42:07,841
It's 100% addictive and kills
one out of every seven users.

428
00:42:07,925 --> 00:42:09,176
Don't mess with it.

429
00:42:09,260 --> 00:42:13,222
I don't mess with drugs no more,
you know that.

430
00:42:15,683 --> 00:42:20,688
It's a liquid-based blue crystalline
substance with a neurotoxin RAH,

431
00:42:20,771 --> 00:42:24,108
retina-activating hallucinogen.

432
00:42:24,191 --> 00:42:29,113
So, it sort of numbs the senses
and makes the world look better?

433
00:42:29,154 --> 00:42:30,364
That's the high.

434
00:42:30,447 --> 00:42:34,785
The low is it damages the central nervous
system, causes insanity, then death.

435
00:42:34,868 --> 00:42:37,120
On the street it's called the dream.

436
00:42:37,204 --> 00:42:39,289
Thank you.

437
00:42:46,338 --> 00:42:48,423
I'm broke.

438
00:43:03,230 --> 00:43:08,819
You know something, Harley?
In a weird way I'm jealous of you two.

439
00:43:10,570 --> 00:43:12,656
Why's that?

440
00:43:12,739 --> 00:43:18,411
The rest of us work so damn hard at life
and you guys just live it one day at a time.

441
00:43:18,495 --> 00:43:19,704
Yeah.

442
00:43:23,667 --> 00:43:25,752
See ya.

443
00:43:46,606 --> 00:43:49,442
What's with you and the old boots?

444
00:43:49,526 --> 00:43:53,696
Lay off my boots, Harley.
I'm in no fuckin' mood.

445
00:43:55,281 --> 00:43:58,284
Did you have a rough night?

446
00:43:58,368 --> 00:44:01,537
I woke up smellin' the coffee.
Give me a light.

447
00:44:01,663 --> 00:44:05,083
- I thought you quit?
- Just give me a light.

448
00:44:15,802 --> 00:44:18,304
- Whose bike?
- Probably hers.

449
00:44:19,639 --> 00:44:21,724
She ain't got no Harley.

450
00:44:27,647 --> 00:44:29,148
What are you doin'?

451
00:44:29,232 --> 00:44:33,069
It ain't hers,
but I'll bet I know whose it is.

452
00:44:33,903 --> 00:44:36,489
- Whose?
- It's his.

453
00:44:38,241 --> 00:44:41,160
You gotta cross and cut
the red and the green wire.

454
00:44:41,243 --> 00:44:47,541
I know how to hot-wire a bike. Don't
tell me how to hot-wire a goddamn bike.

455
00:44:49,752 --> 00:44:52,421
You gotta turn on the gas.

456
00:44:56,425 --> 00:44:57,843
(bike starts)

457
00:44:59,678 --> 00:45:03,849
If he's gonna take my girl,
I'm gonna take his bike.

458
00:45:22,993 --> 00:45:26,789
- You sure this is the right bank?
- Yeah, I'm sure.

459
00:45:26,872 --> 00:45:30,709
- How sure?
- Hey, man, I'm real sure.

460
00:45:30,793 --> 00:45:35,297
You were real sure there was gonna be
money on that armoured truck.

461
00:45:35,380 --> 00:45:38,717
And you were real sure
this plan was gonna work.

462
00:45:38,801 --> 00:45:43,805
You better be right about this or I'll break
your head so you can't think no more.

463
00:45:43,889 --> 00:45:48,060
Lighten up and tell me
about that guy that's workin' Virginia.

464
00:45:48,143 --> 00:45:49,895
Don't care. Didn't ask.

465
00:45:52,481 --> 00:45:57,152
- You're gonna let her go just like that?
- From where I stand, she let me go.

466
00:45:57,235 --> 00:46:00,739
(Harley) If she wants you to chase her,
that's the game.

467
00:46:00,822 --> 00:46:04,242
My old man used to tell me,
before he left this shitty world,

468
00:46:04,326 --> 00:46:06,495
never chase buses or women.

469
00:46:06,578 --> 00:46:09,081
You always get left behind.

470
00:46:25,013 --> 00:46:28,016
I assume you're here to do business?

471
00:46:28,099 --> 00:46:31,436
I'd like to do some business with you
some other time.

472
00:46:31,519 --> 00:46:34,522
But right now we got to talk
to the man upstairs.

473
00:46:34,606 --> 00:46:36,691
Stay on my tail.

474
00:46:41,196 --> 00:46:43,531
No problem.

475
00:46:56,127 --> 00:47:00,381
Looks like we really
rattled the cage, Marlboro.

476
00:47:06,971 --> 00:47:10,975
- This ain't gonna fly.
- I'll bet you it flies.

477
00:47:13,728 --> 00:47:16,481
- How much?
- I'll bet you a dollar.

478
00:47:17,482 --> 00:47:24,072
If you win you'll have to give me credit
cos that cab fare last night broke me.

479
00:47:25,907 --> 00:47:27,992
If I win, we're dead.

480
00:47:29,994 --> 00:47:31,162
(phone rings)

481
00:47:31,245 --> 00:47:34,999
Strap on your seat belt
and get ready to fly.

482
00:47:36,918 --> 00:47:38,419
American Airlines.

483
00:47:38,502 --> 00:47:42,506
You've got something of mine
and I want it back.

484
00:47:42,590 --> 00:47:45,426
Really? What is that?

485
00:47:45,927 --> 00:47:51,098
You know something,
you've got balls. Big ones.

486
00:47:52,016 --> 00:47:54,769
But they're not as big as you might think.

487
00:47:54,852 --> 00:48:00,024
Well, mister, my balls are big enough
to get your attention.

488
00:48:09,533 --> 00:48:13,787
- What do you want?
- How's about $2.5 million?

489
00:48:15,122 --> 00:48:18,542
Wait a minute. Check that.
I got a little side bet goin'.

490
00:48:18,626 --> 00:48:22,212
Make that $2.5 million plus a buck.

491
00:48:22,713 --> 00:48:24,632
When?

492
00:48:24,715 --> 00:48:25,883
Where?

493
00:48:26,717 --> 00:48:29,303
Airplane graveyard,

494
00:48:30,387 --> 00:48:32,890
